s the main arterial supply to the prostate gland. It arises from the anterior division of the internal iliac artery and gives off prostatic branches that supply both the prostate gland and seminal vesicles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior vesical artery\u003C/strong\u003E primarily supplies the upper portion of the urinary bladder. The \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal pudendal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the external genitalia. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emiddle rectal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the rectum and surrounding tissues. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eobturator artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the adductor muscles of the thigh.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The prostate gland receives its main arterial supply from the inferior vesical artery, a branch of the anterior division of the internal iliac artery","The prostatic branches arise from the inferior vesical artery to supply the prostate and seminal vesicles"],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Gurung P, Yetiskul E, Jialal I. Physiology, Male Reproductive System. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538429/","Foster RA. Male Genital System. Jubb, Kennedy \u0026 Palmer\u0027s Pathology of Domestic Animals: Volume 3. 2016:465\u2013510.e1. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-7020-5319-1.00016-5. Epub 2016 Mar 18. PMCID: PMC7271154","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media","Andersson KE, Boedtkjer DB, Forman A. The link between vascular dysfunction, bladder ischemia, and aging bladder dysfunction. Ther Adv Urol. 2017 Jan;9(1):11-27. doi: 10.1177/1756287216675778. Epub 2016 Nov 4. PMID: 28042309; PMCID: PMC5167073"]},"relationships":{"itemRevi